.TH ASTRAL.STARS 5 "2025-11-26" "Astral 5.3.1.6" "Astral Package Manager"
.SH NAME
astral.stars \- Astral advanced configuration file
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fB/etc/astral/astral.stars\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBastral.stars\fR is an advanced configuration file for the Astral package manager. It uses the .stars format to define complex configuration options.
.SH FILE FORMAT
The file uses the .stars format:

.nf
# Boolean values
option = yes
option = no

# String values
option = "value"

# Comments start with #
.fi

.SH OPTIONS
.SS General
.TP
\fBUSAGE_MODE\fR
Controls help output length: \fBcompact\fR or \fBfull\fR (default: full)

.SS Debug
.TP
\fBdebug\fR
Enable debug mode: \fByes\fR or \fBno\fR (default: no)

.SS Astral-env
.TP
\fBastral_env\fR
Enable astral-env support: \fBenabled\fR or \fBdisabled\fR (default: disabled)

.SS Safety Features
Individual safety features can be toggled:

.nf
safety = {
    script_check = yes
    collision_detect = yes
    checksum_verify = yes
};
.fi

.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
$AST.core: {
    MAKE_CONF = "/etc/astral/make.conf"
    INSTALL_ROOT = "/"
    USAGE_MODE = "full"
    astral-env          = "disabled"
    astral-env-system   = "disabled"
};

# Safety features
safety = {
    script_check = yes
    collision_detect = yes
    ghost_detect = yes
    checksum_verify = yes
    mask_check = yes
};
.fi

.SH FILES
.TP
\fB/etc/astral/make.conf\fR
Main configuration file
.TP
\fB/etc/astral/package.mask\fR
Masked packages

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR astral (1),
.BR make.conf (5)
